<div class="paragraph">
<p>Google GenAI text embeddings API uses dense vector representations.
Unlike sparse vectors, which tend to directly map words to numbers, dense vectors are designed to better represent the meaning of a piece of text.
The benefit of using dense vector embeddings in generative AI is that instead of searching for direct word or syntax matches, you can better search for passages that align to the meaning of the query, even if the passages don&#8217;t use the same language.</p>
