Many modern AI models now provide native support for structured output, which offers more reliable results compared to prompt-based formatting. Spring AI supports this through the <a href="api/chatclient.html#_native_structured_output">Native Structured Output</a> feature.

When using native structured output, the JSON schema generated by <code>BeanOutputConverter</code> is sent directly to the model&#8217;s structured output API, eliminating the need for format instructions in the prompt. This approach provides:

<strong>Higher reliability</strong>: The model guarantees output conforming to the schema
<strong>Cleaner prompts</strong>: No need to append format instructions
<strong>Better performance</strong>: Models can optimize for structured output internally
